This snippet demonstrates how to define API Route Handlers in the Next.js `app` directory, which replace traditional API Routes from the `pages` directory. Route Handlers allow creating custom request handlers for a given route using standard Web Request and Response APIs. Examples are provided for both TypeScript and JavaScript.

