### Handle Webhooks in Next.js Route Handlers

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/route.mdx

Demonstrates how to receive and process POST requests from third-party services. Unlike the Pages Router, Route Handlers do not require manual body parser configuration to access the request payload.

```typescript
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  try {
    const text = await request.text()
    // Process the webhook payload
  } catch (error) {
    return new Response(`Webhook error: ${error.message}`, {
      status: 400,
    })
  }

  return new Response('Success!', {
    status: 200,
  })
}
```

