### Access Dynamic Segment in Server Component - Next.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/dynamic-routes.mdx

Demonstrates how to access dynamic route segment parameters in a Server Component. The params prop is a Promise that must be awaited to extract the dynamic segment value. This example shows a blog post page that receives a slug parameter from the URL.

```typescript
export default async function Page({
  params,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ slug: string }>
}) {
  const { slug } = await params
  return <div>My Post: {slug}</div>
}
```

