### Implement a Dynamic Blog Post Page with Params in Next.js (TSX/JSX)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/01-getting-started/03-layouts-and-pages.mdx

This Next.js page component handles a dynamic route segment `[slug]`. It asynchronously extracts the `slug` from the `params` prop, fetches the corresponding post using `getPost(slug)`, and then renders the post's title and content. This demonstrates how to retrieve and use dynamic route parameters.

```tsx
export default async function BlogPostPage({
  params,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ slug: string }>
}) {
  const { slug } = await params
  const post = await getPost(slug)

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{post.title}</h1>
      <p>{post.content}</p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

