### Generate Next.js Static Params Bottom-Up for Nested Dynamic Routes (TSX/JSX)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/generate-static-params.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to generate static parameters for multiple dynamic segments, such as `[category]` and `[product]`, from the child route segment's `page.tsx` or `page.js` file. The `generateStaticParams` function fetches a list of products and maps them to an array of objects, where each object contains the `category` slug and `product` ID for pre-rendering.

```tsx
// Generate segments for both [category] and [product]
export async function generateStaticParams() {
  const products = await fetch('https://.../products').then((res) => res.json())

  return products.map((product) => ({
    category: product.category.slug,
    product: product.id,
  }))
}

export default function Page({
  params,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ category: string; product: string }>
}) {
  // ...
}
```

